{
  "stem": "25651.9",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Uncle Zeev wrote, Perla says you should come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Come.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So finally-- you know, I told you my mother had this abortion, probably 1934ish or so. '35 was the Maccabiah, and there were cheap tickets.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she went in '35.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She arrives and my uncle says to her, I just got a telegram whilst you were already on the way that there is a new cure for tuberculosis of the nerve endings.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I have sent Perla to Switzerland to my brother, this address that I had throughout the war of the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I've just sent her to Switzerland for a cure.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother arrives at the flat where they lived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She sees there's no woman here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she gets hold of an Arab woman and she starts cleaning, you know, getting organized.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she has two tickets for her and Perla to go to the Maccabiah.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Perla isn't here, so she takes Itzchak, my eldest cousin, the eldest-- Itzchak Chari the eldest son.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it's-- I don't know if you know Ramat Gan in Tel Aviv.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was a new stadium built for the Maccabiah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the stadium is still there in Ramat Gan.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Itzchak now tells me, they arrive at the Maccabiah and Arab youths are throwing stones.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the Haganah comes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in those days, in '35, they had sticks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They didn't-- you know, it wasn't like the army in those days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they started beating up on these Arab kids.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And Itzchak says, your mother gets off the bus shrieking away, folding her parasol, and she is hitting the Haganah youths with her parasol, shouting in them-- at them in Yiddish, [YIDDISH], you don't beat small children.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You see, the Haganah was fighting Arab youths who were throwing stones, at [INAUDIBLE] buses.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
